# Raspberry Pi Programs

### `manage26V17.py`

Main vehicle-control program.

It handles:

* DonkeyCar recording
* Autonomous model driving
* Raspberry Pi camera input
* PS4 controller input
* DYNAMIXEL steering and throttle
* Sense HAT model selection
* Gyro-based lap tracking
* Obstacle parking exit
* Camera preview
* Tub-record deletion
* Safe shutdown

Available modes:

```bash
 manage26V17.py --recording
 manage26V17.py --driving
 manage26V17.py --driving-view
 manage26V17.py --driving-skip
 manage26V17.py --driving-view-skip
```

Driving modes:

* `FCW` — Free Run clockwise
* `FCCW` — Free Run counterclockwise
* `OCW` — Obstacle Run clockwise
* `OCCW` — Obstacle Run counterclockwise

A mode can also be selected directly:

```bash
%Run manage26V17.py --driving
```

---

### `dynamixel_functions.py`

DYNAMIXEL motor-control program used for testing.

Main functions:

```python
run_position(motor_id, speed, angle)
run_for_seconds(motor_id, speed, seconds)
run_for_degrees(motor_id, speed, degrees)
```

The file can also be imported into another Python program.

---

## Hardware Settings

| Setting           |          Value |
| DYNAMIXEL port    | `/dev/ttyUSB0` |
| Baud rate         |        `57600` |
| Protocol          |          `2.0` |
| Throttle motor ID |            `1` |
| Steering motor ID |            `2` |

The programs use different steering-center values:

| File                     | Steering center |
| `manage26V17.py`         |          `3060` |
| `dynamixel_functions.py` |          `3126` |
---

## Required Hardware

* Raspberry Pi
* U2D2
* 2 DYNAMIXEL XL330 motors
* Raspberry Pi Camera
* Sense HAT
* PS4 controller for recording mode

---

## Required Python Packages

```text
donkeycar
tensorflow
numpy
pygame
dynamixel-sdk
sense-hat
picamera
```
